---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Coding Benchmarks" activePage="coding" description="LRU cache, FastAPI, and LeetCode coding benchmark results for local LLMs on AMD Strix Halo">
  <div class="page-header fade-up">
    <h1>Coding Benchmarks</h1>
    <p class="description">Three coding benchmark suites: a thread-safe LRU cache implementation, a FastAPI REST API generator, and algorithmic LeetCode problems.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>LRU Cache with TTL (10 Unit Tests)</h2>
  <div class="card fade-up">
    <p>Implements a thread-safe LRU cache with TTL support. Validated by 10 unit tests covering get/put, expiration, capacity eviction, thread safety, and edge cases.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="table-wrap fade-up">
    <table class="sortable">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Model</th>
          <th>Backend</th>
          <th data-type="number">Tests</th>
          <th data-type="number">Time</th>
          <th>Notes</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Qwen3-30B-Instruct-2507 <span class="badge champion">Champion</span></td><td>AMDVLK</td><td class="best">10/10</td><td>12s</td><td>Perfect, fastest</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Kimi-Linear-48B Q4_K_M</td><td>AMDVLK</td><td class="best">10/10</td><td>11s</td><td>Fastest perfect</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Kimi-Linear-48B Q5_K_M (b8055)</td><td>AMDVLK</td><td class="best">10/10</td><td>14s</td><td>Conv state fix improved reliability</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Qwen3-Coder-Next-80B</td><td>AMDVLK</td><td class="best">10/10</td><td>25s</td><td>Coding-focused variant</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Qwen3.5-9B Q8_0</td><td>RADV</td><td class="best">10/10</td><td>30s</td><td>No-think mode, fastest Qwen3.5</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">GPT-OSS-120B</td><td>ROCm</td><td class="best">10/10</td><td>51s</td><td>Perfect</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Qwen3.5-35B-A3B UD-Q4_K_XL (thinking)</td><td>RADV</td><td class="best">10/10</td><td>148s</td><td>Thinking ON, Unsloth params, 64k ctx</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Qwen3.5-35B-A3B AesSedai-Q4 (defaults)</td><td>AMDVLK</td><td class="best">10/10</td><td>158s</td><td>MoE-aware quant preserves coding</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Qwen3.5-35B-A3B UD-Q4_K_XL (no-think)</td><td>RADV</td><td class="best">10/10</td><td>195s</td><td>No-think, Unsloth params</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Qwen3.5-122B-A10B UD-Q4_K_XL (thinking)</td><td>RADV</td><td class="best">10/10</td><td>422s</td><td>Thinking ON, Unsloth params, 64k ctx</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Qwen3.5-122B-A10B Unsloth-UD-Q4 (defaults)</td><td>AMDVLK</td><td class="best">10/10</td><td>517s</td><td>Mar 5 imatrix update</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Qwen3.5-27B UD-Q4_K_XL (Unsloth params)</td><td>RADV</td><td class="best">10/10</td><td>527s</td><td>Was 0/10 with default params</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Qwen3.5-4B Q8_0</td><td>RADV</td><td>9/10</td><td>24s</td><td>TTL init bug</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Nemotron-3-Nano-30B</td><td>AMDVLK</td><td>7/10</td><td>30s</td><td>Missing imports</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Ministral-3-14B-Instruct</td><td>AMDVLK</td><td>6/10</td><td>37s</td><td>Minor edge case bugs</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Devstral-Small-2-24B</td><td>ROCm</td><td>2/10</td><td>36s</td><td>TTL handling bugs</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Devstral-2-123B</td><td>RADV</td><td>2/10</td><td>204s</td><td>Size didn't help</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">GLM-4.7-Flash-Opus-Distill</td><td>RADV</td><td>2/10</td><td>35s</td><td>Distillation didn't fix coding</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Ling-Flash-2.0</td><td>RADV</td><td>2/10</td><td>80s</td><td>Logic bugs</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Mistral-Large-2411</td><td>AMDVLK</td><td>2/10</td><td>291s</td><td>Mistral models struggle here</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">GPT-OSS-20B-Derestricted</td><td>RADV</td><td class="badge failed">0/10</td><td>16s</td><td>Missing imports</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">MiniMax-M2.5 IQ3_XXS</td><td>RADV</td><td class="badge failed">0/10</td><td>138s</td><td>Missing imports, logic correct</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Qwen3.5-27B (Q8 / Q4, default params)</td><td>RADV</td><td class="badge failed">0/10</td><td>600s</td><td>Thinking consumed tokens; fixed with Unsloth params (10/10)</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Step3.5-Flash IQ3_XS</td><td>RADV</td><td class="badge failed">0/10</td><td>420s</td><td>Quant degraded imports</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Solar-Open-100B</td><td>RADV</td><td class="badge failed">0/10</td><td>164s</td><td>All reasoning, no code</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <h2>FastAPI TODO List (8 Functional Tests)</h2>
  <div class="card fade-up">
    <p>Generates a complete FastAPI REST API for a TODO list, then validates it with 8 functional tests covering CRUD operations, error handling, and auto-incrementing IDs.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="table-wrap fade-up">
    <table class="sortable">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Model</th>
          <th data-type="number">Tests</th>
          <th data-type="number">Time</th>
          <th>Notes</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="model-name">GPT-OSS-120B</td><td class="best">8/8</td><td>48s</td><td>Proper DTO pattern (TodoCreate, TodoUpdate)</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Magistral-Small-2509</td><td class="best">8/8</td><td>265s</td><td>Proper DTOs, very slow (reasoning)</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Qwen3-30B-Instruct-2507</td><td>2/8</td><td>9s</td><td>Single model, requires id in POST</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Qwen3-Next-80B</td><td>2/8</td><td>49s</td><td>Same issue</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Nemotron-3-Nano-30B</td><td>2/8</td><td>20s</td><td>Same issue</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="insight fade-up">
    <p><strong>Key insight:</strong> This benchmark tests prompt adherence as much as coding ability. The prompt specifies <code>POST /todos</code> accepts <code>{'{"title": "..."}'}</code> &mdash; only the 120B+ models used proper DTO patterns. Smaller models defaulted to a single model requiring <code>id</code> in POST.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <h2>LeetCode (Algorithmic Problems)</h2>
  <div class="card fade-up">
    <p>Tests algorithmic coding across easy, medium, and hard LeetCode-style problems: Two Sum, 3Sum, Container With Most Water, Trapping Rain Water, Merge K Sorted Lists, and more.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="table-wrap fade-up">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Model</th>
          <th>Easy</th>
          <th>Medium</th>
          <th>Hard</th>
          <th>Total</th>
          <th>Time</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="model-name">Nemotron-3-Nano-30B <span class="badge perfect">Perfect</span></td><td class="best">5/5</td><td class="best">22/22</td><td class="best">32/32</td><td class="best">59/59</td><td>71s</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="insight fade-up">
    <p><strong>Key insight:</strong> Nemotron-3-Nano's LRU cache failure (7/10 above) is specific to complex multi-requirement systems code, not general coding ability. Reasoning tokens excel at step-by-step algorithmic problem solving.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <h2>Coding Rankings</h2>
  <ul class="findings fade-up">
    <li><strong>Qwen3-30B dominates</strong> &mdash; 10/10 in 12s, 4x faster than the next perfect scorer.</li>
    <li><strong>Qwen3.5-9B is the fastest Qwen3.5</strong> &mdash; 10/10 in 30s (vs 148s for 35B thinking, 422s for 122B thinking).</li>
    <li><strong>Thinking mode speeds up coding</strong> &mdash; 35B: 148s thinking vs 195s no-think. 122B: 422s thinking vs 517s defaults. Thinking helps plan the implementation.</li>
    <li><strong>Qwen3.5-27B FIXED with Unsloth params</strong> &mdash; was 0/10 (thinking consumed all tokens). With <code>enable_thinking:false</code> and Unsloth sampling params: 10/10 in 527s.</li>
    <li><strong>Sampling params are critical</strong> &mdash; <code>--reasoning-budget 0</code> does NOT work for Qwen3.5. Must use <code>--chat-template-kwargs '&#123;"enable_thinking":false&#125;'</code>.</li>
    <li><strong>Model size doesn't guarantee coding quality</strong> &mdash; Devstral-2-123B scored the same 2/10 as the 24B version.</li>
  </ul>

  <script is:inline>
    document.querySelectorAll('table.sortable th').forEach((th, i) => {
      const arrow = document.createElement('span');
      arrow.className = 'sort-arrow';
      arrow.textContent = ' \u25B4';
      th.appendChild(arrow);
      let asc = true;
      th.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const table = th.closest('table');
        const tbody = table?.querySelector('tbody');
        if (!table || !tbody) return;
        const rows = Array.from(tbody.querySelectorAll('tr'));
        const isNum = th.dataset.type === 'number';
        table.querySelectorAll('.sort-arrow').forEach(a => { a.classList.remove('active'); a.textContent = ' \u25B4'; });
        arrow.classList.add('active');
        arrow.textContent = asc ? ' \u25B4' : ' \u25BE';
        rows.sort((a, b) => {
          const av = a.children[i]?.textContent?.trim() ?? '';
          const bv = b.children[i]?.textContent?.trim() ?? '';
          if (isNum) return asc ? parseFloat(av) - parseFloat(bv) : parseFloat(bv) - parseFloat(av);
          return asc ? av.localeCompare(bv) : bv.localeCompare(av);
        });
        rows.forEach(r => tbody.appendChild(r));
        asc = !asc;
      });
    });
  </script>
</BaseLayout>
